<td valign="top" width="263"> <p style="line-height: 1.3em; color: #00253e; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 0; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="color: #000000;"><strong><a href="https://cote.io/2019/03/22/containers-are-mostly-just-for-large-enterprises/" target="_blank" id="" style="color: #000000;">Containers are mostly just for large enterprises</a> (Michael Coté):</strong> Some interesting findings from KeyBanc suggesting that many companies are cooling on containers, perhaps because containers (as broadly defined) aren’t what companies thought they’d be.&nbsp;</span></p> </td> 
